  "Hexane is magnetic and repels the charged balloon while water molecules are not magnetic": "",
  "The balloon only works on liquids that have a temperature below twenty degrees Celsius": "",
  "Polar molecules like water have partial charges that are attracted to the charged balloon, causing the stream to bend. Nonpolar hexane molecules have no significant partial charges, so they are not deflected.": "",
  "A nail polish remover dissolves nail polish quickly but does not mix well with water. Based on this, what can you conclude about nail polish and the remover?": "",
